<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dirty Tricks:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Because, technically speaking, Dirty Tricks is a spell, It has issues at high level RvR because it is a level 20 spell. I propose the following changes to Dirty Tricks to improve its usefulness:<br>
<br>
1: Lower the timer to 15 Minutes<br>
<br>
2: Create 3 Levels of the spell. <br>
<br>
Level 20 - Flub - Increases fumble rate on target<br>
Level 35 - Bungle - Increases fumble rate on target<br>
Level 48 - Fumble - Increases fumble rate on target<br>
<br>
If these changes were implemented, it would actually make the ability useful. Targets cannot resist the crits from a Berserk, nor the extra damage from the magical third sword of a Blademaster. A stinging cloud of dust, obscuring one's vision should not be resistable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Charge:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This needs to have its speed increased, and needs to not automatically turn into sprint. Perhaps modifying the spell so that it works similar to the Ranger's escape spell would be a satisfactory change.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Flurry:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
No animation currently. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Styles:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dual Wield:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Flank needs to have a to-hit bonus. <br>
<br>
Penumbra should be changed from one of the 2 chains off of Shadow's Edge to be the 2nd in the chain off of Misty Gloom.<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
Dual Shadows should have its positional requirement removed, and added to chain off of Misty Gloom.<br>
<br>
Increase bleed damage on styles.<br>
<br>
Dual Wield should be an advanced weapon specialization, similar to 2-handed and Polearm. We should recieve increased damage with an increase in spec, and our Dual Wield styles should do better damage than our base weapon styles. Making this change would make a lot more people consider playing the class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Crush:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Devestate needs to have a stun component<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Equipment Issues:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Please allow shields to be hotkeyed, or allow them to be equipped in the 2H slot for Mercenaries. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Realm Abilities: </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Prevent Flight -- if this were lowered to cost 10 points, it is likely that more Mercenaries would purchase it. That's a lot of RSPS to shell out for a 35% chance to snare.<br>
<br>
Void has basically been superceded by Flurry. <br>
<br>
Determination needs to affect Melee Stuns, as was originally promised.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries currently do not have access to Avoid Pain. They should.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Other Issues:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
During the Beta, Reavers were allowed to obtain Parry at level 5, because they have a Parry Reactional at level 4.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries have an Evade Reactionary at 4. Please grant Evade to Mercenaries at level 5 instead of 10, as there is little in the way of defensive capabilities for someone who is starting out in the class.<br>
<br>
Reavers get Parry at 5, Armsmen at 10, Paladins at 15, and Mercenaries at 17. Besides Evade, Parry is our only means of defense, yet out of all the Fighter classes, we receive it the latest. Please grant Mercenaries Parry at either 5 or 10.<br>
<br>
These proposals are likely too late for the upcoming changes, but hopefully some of them can be incorporated into whatever is coming for the class.      <p><img border=0 src="http://www.blargle.com/daoc/h-merc.jpg" /><BR>
